column9: Were you able to complete your task?
column10: Did you submit an order to Scholastic Book Clubs during this visit?
column11: Did you experience any difficulties on the site today?
column12: How likely are you to recommend Scholastic Book Clubs to a friend?
column14: Comments
It wasn’t clear to me once on the checkout page how to get back to the browsing area. Not a large problem for me but it could be frustrating for someone who struggles with executive function.

In December, I did not receive the email letting me (teacher) know that a parent submitted an online order until February. This resulted in the family not receiving their books in a timely manner and books were no longer available to be purchased.    Saturday, March 18th, I received an email letting me (teacher) know that I had an online order. When I logged in to submit it, the cart is empty.     I'm very frustrated with this online process and am just recently having issues with it.
Love Scholastic!

Love scholastic books! I had them as a child growing up and love that it is still available to my child. He loves looking through the little paper flyer they receive in school and always has a list for us to buy! Would much rather contribute to this than just going buying books at Walmart or other big chain stores
Happy!

Thank you for have the book of the week for $1.00 and the 5 for five deals. It really helps when you are purchasing for the classroom with donated funds. I am able to give each student in my class one book a month.

Will be awesome if we receive a notification when the teacher receive the other and submit the order, last year I submit the order but not received the books because the teacher don't receive our order
Taking items out of the shopping cart and putting them into the wish list is a pain.
Still looking for gender neutral or transgender books on your site with no luck.
Always Quick and Easy to Use
It is easier to navigate on my computer but I usually use my phone and it was difficult to check out on my phone and had to use my computer.

I find that even when there money in my account it shows pending for a week or more and in the past only some of my books have arrived due them taking so long and I guess because I used a gift card they didn’t understand how to split tender my order or something but the prices are useally reasonable
Why is it taking a over a month to get my order when I could simply order off another website and have it in two days
Failed initial order weeks ago with no notification, logged in and books in cart had disappeared then reappeared today, went through today
I have not ordered in several years however I had many bonus points at that time and they"ve disappeared

It was difficult to click apply and submit when trying to apply the promo code for a $5 free book. And I am disappointed that it doesn’t allow to apply the code more than once. I feel it should apply to every $25 spent.
Kids books should not be so expensive
I love your company.  You have always been accommodating.
awesome
I LOVE that when I choose a book from the flyer and then choose continue shopping, it takes me RIGHT BACK to where I was!  Good job!!
I wish scholastic would have the floor puzzle you use to sell, Like the pout pout fish puzzle.

I love Scholastic but it's gotten a bit expensive.  I can go to a store and grab the same books and have them instantly for about the same price.  That worries me for Scholastic because I have always been a scholastic cheerleader!
Lovely, thank you
hi I am poop
The site was teacher friendly. I was able to create an account .
I love supporting my child’s school, and the cost of books is often cheaper than what I would find on Amazon!
I love ship to home.
I tried to search for fairy tale books for a unit in my classroom. Books that I had previously ordered and wanted to replace, due to student use, are no longer available.
The page wouldn't load at times.
Need more diversity of view points in your book offering.  Should include the Tuttle twins series and books reflective of more religious view points, Catholic, Muslim, Buddhist etc.
Would like to see more variety. Seems like a lot of it is based off of famous characters.
The reminder to add teacher was helpful
Looking to order the Dragon Master Series Books 18 through 25
Wonderfully made and thank you for helping my daughter find a love of reading
I occasionally have issues with the site glitching or reloading while i am working on it
It's not very user friendly.   It would be nice to see the books you've already purchased.  Also, it would be nice to have more bilingual spanish/english books.
The mobile device site is very difficult to navigate.  It was hard to find the student order that needed to be submitted.
Every time I place a class order, I need to re-learn how to find it. I would love it if signing in would bring me directly to my teacher site instead of my "parent" view.
This was probably one of the easiest shopping experiences I've had with school related vendors.
My deadline for students is in two days.  I was just browsing what I wanted to get.
Had a hard time finding books for beginning readers.
My whole order with the birthday coupons about 20 of them disappeared. The customer service agent was great! but it was super frustrating
site was a little low when I entered payment info.  I might have hit continue checkout twice.
Sometimes the books that are most current are not available.   What kids want to read isn't always an option.  I believe more children's input would benefit the company.
Out of stock items and texts that I was seeking not available through Scholastic.
I really like that this websie is so easy to use.
Love having your books available to our kids at school!
I just hope I will receive my iPad when I order it! Please add Spanish and bilingual books to the regular flyers.
Excellence
Have loved being part of the Scholastic Book Orders for many years!  Great company!

Some of the books on the list we were given from my child’s teacher were not on this website so we could not order them. We were told that orders ship directly to our address, but we have come to find out that they need to be shipped to a teacher, and the process to do so is rather confusing.
Easy search & add. Like the related suggested titles
I was looking for a specific book, "Westing Game" and you didn't have it. When will you have it in stock? Thank you.
Thank you.

My order that was placed on Feb. 1, 2023, has been LOST. I'm trying to track the shipment, but NO luck. The 25-digit tracking number is a HASSLE to follow on the shipping app. So, I guess I need to be reimbursed for the order I placed.
Everything was great!
I love that I can still support the classroom every month through the wishlist

I found it difficult to find the correct website where I could see copies of the flyers. When I logged in initially there was no tab for looking at the flyers.  Is that the difference between the regular Scholastic website and the Book Club website?
I was just browsing to spend my classroom points.
I really love the scholastic program and appreciate the resources for my families at home and the ones for my  classroom as well.
Book quality and selection has gone down - disappointed.
Make the wish lists shareable to others so I can share with family who wants to buy my kids books
I wish you would give more detail  about the books.
Request that Club Leo be monthly, just like your other book clubs.  It is very hard to get parents books in spanish for my Dual Language Class.  Thank you

Could we bring back the $20 free per month, instead of breaking it up to $10 this month and $10 then next month??  With $20 together, you can buy more interesting things for your classroom, like things for centers from the bonus catalog, etc.
Could not find books one way… Tried another way and found them
love the bonus points

I used my teacher email and my regular password, but I was taken to the page that parents would see, not my teacher page.  It says Welcome to Mrs. Bolhofner's classroom, but the account name at the top says STACY, not Mrs. Stacy Bolhofner.  I don't know what I did wrong because I used the correct email and password for my teacher account.

I would like to be able to look up books according to reading level specific instead of just age level or grade level.  My daughter is in the first grade but her AR score is 2.5 to 3.5. When I look up second grade level books sometimes I get 3.8 AR  level books. It makes searching for books a little more difficult.
very easy to order books!
NA Thank You!
Teachers cannot afford expensive books and parents have stopped ordering books. Update the books and lower the prices.
I may stop sending book orders home because I work in a low income school and I may not get $25 worth of orders each month and I do not want to have to foot the shipping
I wish there was a way to prevent parents ordering pass the due date. I have been missing orders.

The site is not user friendly on mobile, especially looking at the fliers. You don't offer as many good deals as you did in the past.  I remember always having a dollar book on each flier. Now they are twice the price....not as appealing. Quite frankly a lot of the books are cheaper on Amazon or secondhand. Only reason I purchase is to support my kid's school. I think that if I add an item to my cart and it is on special you should honor that price. I don't have control over when the teacher places the order. Teachers are overburdened with so much it is hard for them to stay on top of option tasks such as these orders. They do their best. Us parents too. It is hard to make time to browse through choose books and have them removed because it was not put in on time...which is out of my control. Every day shopping from schoolastic is a tougher choice when  it is quicker to order from Amazon who can deliver pretty quickly and at a better price. They also offer more options like complete se
Thank you for running deals and making it affordable to order my kids books!
Difficulty with flyers
One book was out of stock. This is probably the last order for the year.
Couldn’t find my other 2 kids teachers so I put it all under one child.
Site is easy to navigate
I find thr layout of the website not as user friendly as it could be.
Login fails to load properly, very bad experience
Just horrible
I love the ship to home option!

I recieved this email and there were no student orders pending:  Dear Terri,    There are student online order(s) in your cart to submit.    SUBMIT STUDENT ORDERS NOW    For your convenience and to get books in the hands of kids, orders $25+ placed by families in February will be submitted automatically at 11:59 p.m. ET on March 31, if you have signed in this school year.    Your Book Box will ship FREE and arrive in your classroom within 5–7 business days after it ships (you will receive a shipping confirmation email).    Already submitted? Please disregard this email.     Questions? Please email us at bookclubs@scholastic.com or call 1-800-724-6527.    Happy reading!  Your friends at Scholastic Book Clubs
Thank you for the coupons and the ability to earn books for my class. Through Scholastic Book Clubs I can give something more tangible than candy a book that will last much longer.
Thank you for offering books at a special rate.  The books that I am ordering today will be given away to children at a low income school at the end of the school year to promote summer reading.
Discount pop ups that did not apply to the child/school order
I appreciate how Scholastic makes it very easy to enter not only student orders but my own teacher order as well.
Easy and carefree!
Had to pause order and find Class/Teacher code
My one student order was not enough to get free shipping so I asked that parent to wait for next month.
I don't know my teachers class code
Easy to complete.
I wish it was easier to get detailed descriptions of the books available with the READS code
The site and the company has gone downhill. The site is hard to navigate. The selection of books has gone downhill.

I had a hard time figuring out I needed to be in the book club portion of the website, I got all the way to shipping of check out to figure out that it would come to my house instead of the teacher before I realized I was in the wrong spot.
It took forever to get my order through.

I wanted to buy a few books to teach my son about Africa, Asia, and Europe… especially focusing on cultural themes, cities, and geography. I had a hard time finding anything like that, and did not end up purchasing anything to satisfy that part of my search. I did but some other books.
Loved it
I just wanted to order the same book for two different children, but I can only order the same book for 1 child.
The site is awesome, great book selection by grade level.

I wish the birthday coupons were $6 to match the raise in prices- most books are too expensive for the coupons now.  There use to be many $4, $4.50, and $5 books, but now there are only a few books at this price point.
I absolutely LOVE scholastic!  Thank you for making your books so affordable and easy for our families to order, and giving our school free books!!
Long time loading during check out... Not a big deal
The search engine is limited

I had a payment of $80 in form of a parent check lost and I was told that due to the large number of orders in December, there was a delay in processing payments. It is now 3 months later. I am not sure if I should have parents write out another check or wait a few more months in case it turns up? I do not want to have the parents stop payment since there is a charge for that at their bank.
It is hard at times to navigate and find the books you want.

When selecting a book with free $10, there needs to be some more sorting options.  Having only 10 per page and 76 pages is very time consuming, especially when the search doesn't necessarily stay when you click to sort by a column.
the site is super easy to navigate
I love all the variety of books you offer and for a great price too!  Easy way to build my child's home library .
Kept hitting previous by mistake. Should be separate from next button
I love scholastic books for my classroom and family.
My coupon was expired.  Maybe give more time to use our coupon codes.

When the notice appeared that told me that I have earned $10 to spend, that notice should also offer the option to make choices right then and there. Not have to get all the way to my cart and almost check out before I'm able to make my selections.
I just feel that since Covid, timing on receiving books has been quite slow.
I was glad to find the Bad Seed collection, so yay!
I wish we would be able to carry forward any unused "Spend right now" money.
The website is so easy to use. great books! thank you!
easier if free shipping for teachers. parents are not able to all offer to buy a book and total is under 25.00 and the teacher has to pay shipping. that becomes costly.
Keep up the great work!! Love this company so much!!
NA
There is no way to check ewallet balances  I can't add my child to my profile without the teacher 's name.    These are simple, basic tools that should be in the programming.   Very poor website.
We love scholastic
I don’t like when your families order and pay and I’m holding the order until the due date and in that time books become unavailable
Selection menus require odd scrolling on the page to view bottom options in the list.

My name is not being printed on the shipping label anymore, only the school name.  We have more than one teacher at our school who orders from Scholastic, so it is necessary to have the teacher's name on the outside of the box.  The last 3 orders did not have my name on the box.  It would be helpful if my name is on there.
not sure if it was website or my computer, unable to see confirmation order
Love the code for a free book!
ordered for my grandson- loved this program when i was a child 1960's as well as my children- 1980's- we LOVE BOOKS!
The dollar book I wanted I was unable to order or find a replacement
My daughter still had some funds on her ewallet, but there was no option for me to use those funds for my purchase.
Everything is all over the place it is so difficult to get to the e wallet.. its very confusing

I'm simply trying to order something from our Scholastic Book Fair!  I'm the school librarian, but yet, you insist I tell you my grade and all that!  I 'm just trying to go into my account, like I've done in the past, and allow a nephew to order some books.   Don't bother contacting me.  I'll give up by them.  This is the account I used before.  I had them put books into the cart and wala!  It was done, but this is ridiculous!  I'm not a teacher or admin.  What other choices do I have?
unable to enter card info for purchase attempted two cards, was only able to use paypal which I prefer not to use.
The prices of books are great!
It kept deleting my bonus book pics every time I had to go back ...

I wish there were more true decodable readers such as Bob Books available on your website. I see lots of Leveled Books based on the cueing system and not decodable books that my Kindergarteners can actually read. Scholastic makes Bob Books so I am not sure why they are no longer available on the website.

This was a very frustrating process.  Not easy to navigate - and search for books once I realized how many I would receive free.  It took an hour to put in an order for 1 child - the other two ordered online.  As a director, I do not really have time for this.
The website kept logging me out. I wish there was an option to stay logged in rather than automatically being logged out. Very frustrating!
When typing the in the search bar, words pop up and cover the search bar so I’m not able to see what I’m typing.
Some trouble finding past orders and lists.
My student has still not received order from before Valentine's Day.
Very easy to use!

My difficulties have been with the billing dept. Our school secretary sent payment for an order that I am still being billed for. Your company does this with the Let's Find Out subscriptions, too-you send monthly statements for the majority of the school year when the school has sent payment in late July/August.   I stopped ordering from your company for several years for this very reason. I guess we are at that point again.
It is the best website ever. It is like an online library.
It was hard to find where to enter the book code from the flyer.
Had trouble editing a student's name
Kept freezing on my phone, so I switched to desktop

I am a kindergarten teacher and I have been ordering from your company for many years and  have depended on you for books and CDs to use in my listening center.  I was really disappointed to not find any new additions.  I am also missing using my points to get new floor puzzles.  Will either of these be coming back?
I wish our wishlists lasted a little longer. At least for the year.
very continent site to navigate. all flyers are available and options are great.
easy to use!
Site is super slow!
would like status on delivery or estimated time
Your coupon codes suck.  Tried multiple and wouldn’t take them.
Thank you for your help.
I submitted my order without being prompted to pay.
unclear understanding of 'tracking' procedure/location if items have not been shipped...    - wondering if the size of the order is connected to the expediency of shipping...
would like to see the book when i enter the code, rather than simply add to cart

I have finally figured it out but for awhile it was hard to determine how to switch from one of my children to the other for an order. I know now that you have to click directly on their name. I think there should be a clear designation such as "click here to switch to a different child's classroom".   Another way for the site to be more user friendly would be if a list of $5 books came up when you type in the READS promo code...or for one of the $5 books already in your cart to automatically switch to free. I did see that there is a section called $5 books that you can scroll through when shopping but I found that after the fact.
Very glitches. Could use categories. Couldn't add to wish list due to  glitches
Could provide choices for 5$ book to make it easier.
I sincerely appreciate the Bonus Points system to help supply books to my classroom without me having to pay for every book myself.
Where do I load just money to my kids account

I had hoped to see a list of the available free $5 books before checking out but I didn't realize that it was a super extensive list and just had to add the READS code to see everything. Not a big problem but I spent a few extra minutes trying to figure that out.
I am frustrated that I no longer receive paper flyers monthly

It was tricky to navigate today--and I generally don't have any trouble with your site. It was difficult to order from flyers and then navigate to the next flyer. It also didn't take my selection for my $10 to spend right now--although it did allow me to select for my coupon $10.
It took me a few minutes to get to the page to set a due date, but that could be me.

When I went to check it, it told me that I was not able to ship to my home address, but I did not have my home address listed as shipping to that address, it automatically populated my child's school address. So I had to restart the process again.

I like that I can find other options for my 3rd grader besides what's in the flyers. Didn't make a purchase as books are repeats from previous flyers, too large of a collection, not of interest or too expensive. I don't want to pay $13 for a hardcover book paperback please.
I had a hard time finding where the free Cat Kid comic book is.
My child's teacher is not listed and a code as needed.  Why did it not come home with my child?
fine
Thanks for offering great books to our students at reasonable prices!
Hard to find books how the site is organized. I had to pay for sakes tax where I wouldn't if I had used a paper order form.
Password trouble
I got a separate email that I need to pay for the order that was already submitted, but I don't see a place to do that on the website.
The cart page didn’t show the buying list properly after deleting.

Would have liked to see books available as free books with pictures of covers of books and not just a list of titles.  Difficult for child to select free book.    Child picked one with title she liked.   Really would have enjoyed looking at cover selections to help choose free book.   Thanks for your consideration.
N/a

I have to sign in every time I go to the site. Also, with reminders, sending home order forms I am not receiving orders. It seems like I am wasting my time. Maybe it is because I am at a Title I school and parents do not spend money on books?
The flyers were not loading
I had picked a $4 free book but had to instead go back through a list to pick one. You should be able to enter a book $5 or under and with code it is automatically made free
excellent service and website. Easy to use and navigate
it keeps telling me to change my password but won't let me change it
The email prompt with the link and teacher’s code was so easy to order through.

viewing the digital flyer is difficult now with the added footers and headers that you have.  I can not zoom in to see the flyers easier either.    I have to continue to request catalogs after I have already placed orders for my classes.

I was ordering from my tablet and the screen was not the same as a computer. There were parts of the page left and right side cut off.   Also, I know about inflation, but some of the books are very expensive now.
The bonus points code was listed as expired.  The person I chatted with added them into my acct.
One of my coupon codes didn't work. I called and they gave me a new code to enter.

This has been incredibly frustrating. I keep receiving invoices saying that I need to pay for my order, however, there is NO place to submit payment/you already have all of my card details, so I'm unsure what else I am supposed to do.
Entered book orders but didn't submit, waiting for Friday.
I could not easily find the book of the week.
I could not find what I was looking for.
I enjoy the books selection
send money to my daughter
Something is odd with putting passwords in. I couldn't remember my password, and it didn't bring up saved ones until after I put a wrong password it.
Scholastics should make all orders free shipping. There are times students only order $20 of books and shipping has to be paid. Many times, parents canceled order because we don't have $25 of books.
the first filter I did on the bonus points section did not show me the things that cost more points, I had to do more filters to get to the most expensive stuff.
I wish it was easier to view books from other age groups. The baby and toddler group is always so hard to find within the website
No comments
This site does not have easy search aspects. I could not find a series of books that I had ordered in the past and would like more from the same collection.
I am so glad things have become much better at Scholastic!  Scholars enjoy receiving their new books each month and I enjoy how quickly the orders are filled, shipped, and received!  :)
When I went back to order more books, the account closed.  Thankfully, I was able to get back to my cart without having to start over with my order.

Books delayed for over 6 weeks. The order was sent to an inactive account even thought the code entered was correct. After speaking with 3 representatives, I was told they could not expedite the order. This was also the problem with an order placed in October 2022. Clearly there is a problem with the system that should be addressed immediately.
It would be great if any coupon sent to me was automatically added to my e-account & popped up with the order rather than me having to find my paper copy and enter the coupon number.

It was not clear of the Bonus points I wanted to add to my account that I needed to place a minimum order of  $25.00.  Scholastic may want to make it very plan in the future to your educators.  Thank you for all the things you do to keep educators and our families reading!!     God Bless you all, Ramelle

From a school standpoint, our main goal is to save enough points to order Christmas books for teachers to give as gifts. We are a Christian school and will continue to do this as long as you offer religious Christmas books. They have been dwindling the past few years and are harder to find. The packs are great when we are ordering for over 100 kids.

The money I added for my son was not on here. Spent 5 calls trying to find where money is, even though I have egift card # and pin #. Lost $25 for all this and child still has no books. Will not EVER order again from here!

I received a statement via email to make a payment, but there is no apparent online option to do so.  Calling in during business hours is not an option for me.  Having online payment options for statements would be extremely helpful.

Not clear on how to access book club with class code. I didn’t have the flyer just the code and I needed to contact the teacher for directions. Made me feel silly as it was there just not on the main landing page.
this site sucks. i cannot find my wallet and add funds for my child
Easy format and simple order process!   I love that teachers can request books for the classroom as donations!     Great site and program.

There should be an app and I shouldn't have to look at the order forms sent home I should be able to see everything you sell instead of trying to search for books and having crap for luck with the pre k and beginner readers
The site is not user friendly. It should be much simply to  set due date and I can never find where I am going. It's been like this for awhile and I would love a simpler site!
It was extremally easy to use
We love Scholastic!!
I can't sign In!!!!!
Overlapping text, had to refresh multiple times to get it to respond
The website is difficult to navigate. I find it difficult to redeem points and purchase orders online.
As always, the Scholastic site is easy to navigate.
Too many clicks to get the tasks done. Either checking student orders or teacher shopping.

It is frustrating that all of the month's book order form don't come in the same week.  Every time I send an order form home for the month, I get two more order forms (for the same month) 1-2 weeks later.  I would wait to send them all at once, but I never know exactly how many are coming for the month.
I wish you had better quality of literature. I think you need to sell mostly new books and of course Scholastic published books. My children like your choices, though.
My students don't order as many books as they used to in the past.    Using Safari on a Mac, two of the choices in the drop-down menu above are cut off.
Login/Assigned Class is confusing, and Online flyers are cumbersome.
Easy to navigate.  Thank you!
I wot. This book
All went well on my bisit.
Had a lot of shipping issues last year, glad that it seems to be resolved so that we can place class orders again.
The pop up won’t let me select mybook
I wish I could share a wishlist with grandma/family
An app or some way to access the site that is mobile device friendly would be beneficial
The parent page does not match the classroom page, so the shipping and code READS does not work.
Thank you!
When I was looking on a flyer I found a book  but I couldn’t add it to my. Cart
I could not split the order between two teachers.
I am trying to place a book order with the teacher's class account but it is not allowing me to order the 3 books that I am able to locate without using it with the teacher's class account.
Hard to find classic book titles

Why is there a constant disruption of paper flyers? Please keep them coming.  I have had to call and request them 3 years in a row.  If I don't place an order, I still would like flyers for the next round.

I have been trying to continue my checkout from coupons and rewards page for 2 days. It would not link to the next stage. Today I utilized the live chat. The people that helped were very helpful and made this a better experience.  They pushed my order through and helped me make a payment.
I'm always ordering books for  my class. They love to order.
I love Scholastics!
Trying to find books with both English and Spanish. Was not easy to search for or know for sure it had both translations in the book.
The site is not intuitive. Also, please note that your top question on satisfaction does not provide an explanation of the scale.

"We're sorry that your order could not be placed.  If you have further questions, please contact us."  Poor error message.  Can't fix it if I don't know what's wrong.  Called and they couldn't tell me what was wrong or how to fix it.
I would love if any codes could be saved in my account. I recently received an email with a code to use in August-September.
Looking for books with audio (CD). Would love as well as I know many teachers would love options for books that have CDs so that we could put them at our listening centers!
As always, great!
Please bring back books with the audio cd.
I was glad to find the Bad Seed collection, so yay!
Finding the cheap books ($1-$2) could be easier.
I'm looking for the Notebook of Doom, Binder of Doom and ALL the Eerie Elementary books.  You don't have these books, so it appears I'll have to buy them from Amazon.
I can't track my shipment status.

It's bothersome to switch between student/teacher orders and the student store  I'd like to see teacher orders and student orders done on the same screen--perhaps just a drop down to indicate which it is

Your directions and navigation to e-wallet are insufficient. I am trying to add more funds, rolled over a gift card balance into her wallet and now cannot add more funds. Do I buy a gift card? I don’t want to just give my credit card number.

I changed my pw so sub wouldn't have my common pw, Then new pw wouldn't work - but I got in here, so maybe it just took some extra time - trying to get on new magazine account. Scholastic book orders always do a great job and website/ordering is very user friendly.
Could not find student online orders

I absolutely LOVE Scholastic and the way this company provides so much support and so much material for students of all ages to be able to buy and enjoy and array of reading material. The perks teachers get for student orders is amazing as well!!
Emailing the link to order is so much easier then sending home the flyers! Thank you for this service!
It was very user-friendly!
Trying to find books with a CD
When viewing the digital flyer, some of the books popped up when turning pages, even though I did not click on them and my mouse was off to the side.
No option to add funds for book fair.  No option to locate my child’s school.  Terrible website, poor navigation.  Should spend less energy on graphics and more on ability to use.
It is too early to update information for the next school year.
I'm interested in books that are "Catholic School Friendly."
Perfect site to get books for my child
I really liked that you could find the circular that you want to order from, page through it, and just click on what you wanted to order and it took you right to the page.
Allow schools and teachers to be tax exempt
No comments
